  "texts": [
    "That is, the system may provide any information and/or any studies from any source, not necessarily correct, reliable or helpful.",
    "Consequently, it is incumbent upon the researcher to issue commands that are suitable for and helpful in achieving the goals of the study (e.g., \"Explain the notion of philanthropy within the business context\").",
    "Following the command, it is crucial to guarantee a thorough review of the output (check that the produced information by the system is indeed helpful in describing the phenomenon under investigation, in this case the notion of \"philanthropy\").",
    "Nonetheless, it is possible that the AI system generates \"false content,\" such as results from studies that do not actually exist.",
    "The steps to follow in such instances are discussed below."
  ],
